<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880223-0129 </DOCNO><HL> Who's News: Bristol-Myers Co. </HL><SO> </SO><CO> WNEWS BMY </CO><DATELINE> BRISTOL-MYERS Co. (New York)  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Ronald A. Ahrens, formerly president of the Bristol-Myers Products unit of this pharmaceuticals and health products concern, was named president of the company's consumer products group and senior vice president of the parent. He will be responsible for the Bristol-Myers Products, Clairol, Drackett, Bristol-Myers Products Canada and Monarch Crown businesses. Mr. Ahrens, 48 years old, succeeds Nicholas M. Evans, who will retire June 1. Stephen E. Bear, currently senior vice president, marketing and sales, of Bristol-Myers Products, will succeed Mr. Ahrens as president of the unit. </TEXT></DOC>